34:16.418 --> 34:19.004
Bloody hell!

34:46.533 --> 34:49.118
Shall we go, darling?

35:10.267 --> 35:12.018
Very nice.

35:12.019 --> 35:15.271
- She's here, is she?
- Oh, yeah, she's here.

35:15.272 --> 35:17.106
Evening, gentlemen.

35:17.107 --> 35:20.943
How can I be of service to you?

35:20.944 --> 35:25.031
My friend would like to
see Madame Lucienne.

35:26.491 --> 35:28.951
Madame Lucienne?

35:28.952 --> 35:31.079
Madame Lucienne.

35:31.080 --> 35:33.958
She holds a very rigid standard.

35:34.750 --> 35:38.044
- Well, that's all right, isn't it?
- Yes.

35:38.045 --> 35:40.631
Come this way.

35:53.729 --> 35:59.650
You go up the stairs, sir... and
through the first door on your right.

35:59.651 --> 36:02.236
Madame Lucienne will
be with you presently.

36:02.237 --> 36:04.822
- Very gay here.
- Yes.

36:33.854 --> 36:37.064
- Monsieur...?
- Er... Jones.

36:37.065 --> 36:38.691
Jones.

36:38.692 --> 36:42.487
I am very pleased to
make your acquaintance.

36:43.029 --> 36:44.822
I as well.

36:44.823 --> 36:46.282
You are nervous?

36:46.283 --> 36:50.370
No, I just thought we might
become... better acquainted.

36:50.371 --> 36:54.166
Oh, mon chÃ©ri, you are nervous.
There is no need to be.

36:54.167 --> 36:59.338
I will take care of
every little thing.

36:59.922 --> 37:03.675
And every big thing.

37:09.056 --> 37:11.267
Oh...

37:11.268 --> 37:14.938
Such a strong man!

37:15.439 --> 37:19.692
Well, yes, I did a bit of sport.
When I was younger, of course.

37:19.693 --> 37:22.320
Oh, but you are still young.

37:22.863 --> 37:24.989
And very strong.

37:24.990 --> 37:28.742
- You want this off as well?
- It is best, no?

37:28.743 --> 37:32.790
The touch of flesh to flesh.

37:32.999 --> 37:35.584
The warmth of the body.

37:36.127 --> 37:39.671
- This is the French way, is it?
- Oui, mon cher.

37:40.256 --> 37:43.341
- What is this?
- A key. But I'm afraid...

37:43.342 --> 37:47.470
Oh, there must be nothing...
nothing between us.

37:47.471 --> 37:50.057
Oh, yes.

37:56.732 --> 37:58.774
Now if you will sit on the lit.

37:58.775 --> 38:03.029
- The what?
- The lit... the bed, the bed, the bed.

38:06.908 --> 38:11.330
Oh, it is so exciting!

38:11.372 --> 38:14.875
You... How do you say...

38:15.626 --> 38:18.212
You inflame me.

38:19.088 --> 38:23.217
But, madame, do you not
remove your own clothing?

38:24.176 --> 38:26.928
Oh, my own... Why, yes, of course.

38:26.929 --> 38:29.431
In just a moment.

38:32.769 --> 38:34.937
- Just a moment.
- Do make haste, madam.

38:34.938 --> 38:37.523
Yes, yes, I will.

38:49.327 --> 38:52.706
Oh, my God, the police!

38:52.707 --> 38:55.084
Quel mess!

39:09.682 --> 39:12.059
Come on, Henry, for God's sake!

39:12.060 --> 39:14.646
I'm coming!

39:15.689 --> 39:18.440
- Police, where are they?
- Downstairs.

39:18.441 --> 39:20.693
- But I could be ruined!
- Quite!

39:20.694 --> 39:23.279
I know the back way.

40:19.755 --> 40:22.882
You couldn't have picked
something more difficult.

40:22.883 --> 40:25.468
- You said you're the bloody best.
- And I am.

40:25.469 --> 40:30.934
But that's the devil's own crib. I've
watched it three days. Look there.

40:31.143 --> 40:35.563
You have to get past those crushers,
then up those stairs in plain sight.

40:35.564 --> 40:38.232
Then into that crib.
Anybody can see you.

40:38.233 --> 40:42.028
Bloody silly. Invitation
to prison, that place is.

40:42.404 --> 40:44.446
What's your pogue up there?

40:44.447 --> 40:47.784
Two Chubb keys in
that green cupboard.

40:51.080 --> 40:53.790
What might they be, them keys?

40:54.417 --> 40:57.920
Two keys that I happen to want.

41:00.840 --> 41:03.383
We're partners, aren't we?

41:03.384 --> 41:07.387
If you're trying to say that you
don't trust me completely...

41:07.388 --> 41:09.973
I don't trust you at all.

41:10.267 --> 41:12.476
Good.

41:12.477 --> 41:17.189
We've been gulling banksmen,
now we're in a railway station.

41:17.190 --> 41:20.443
What's in a station?
Trains is in a...

41:21.069 --> 41:24.071
Mother of God! You're
after the Crimean g...

41:24.072 --> 41:27.449
Trying to rob a moving
train... it can't be done.

41:27.450 --> 41:28.993
Why not?

41:28.994 --> 41:31.663
- It hasn't been done, has it?
- No.

41:31.664 --> 41:34.457
Crimean gold. Mother of God!

41:34.458 --> 41:39.170
That's Â£25,000, isn't it? A big
