41:39.171 --> 41:41.464
- Mother of God!
- Are you ready to go in?

41:41.465 --> 41:43.341
Am I... Yes.

41:43.342 --> 41:45.760
Where's the chavy?

41:45.761 --> 41:48.347
There.

41:49.890 --> 41:52.101
He's your son.

41:52.102 --> 41:54.144
I don't have no son.

41:54.145 --> 41:56.105
Louisa says he's your son.

41:56.106 --> 41:58.107
Hmph! Louisa!

41:58.108 --> 42:00.484
She wouldn't know. Is that him?

42:00.485 --> 42:04.697
He's not my son. He's
too ugly to be my son!

42:06.324 --> 42:08.242
So what's the sweetener?

42:08.243 --> 42:10.829
A guinea.

42:10.955 --> 42:14.291
Well, if he is my son,
he'll be worth it.

42:21.632 --> 42:24.968
- Are we ready?
- Mm!

42:38.942 --> 42:43.779
- Oh, Geoffrey! I've been robbed!
- Stop thief! Stop that boy!

42:44.489 --> 42:47.074
Somebody stop him!

42:47.909 --> 42:50.494
Police! Stop that boy!

42:50.996 --> 42:53.582
Police! Stop that boy!

42:54.542 --> 42:56.960
Stop thief! Stop that boy!

42:56.961 --> 42:59.546
I've got him!

43:09.223 --> 43:13.102
- Stop that boy. He's a thief.
- What's going on?

43:14.104 --> 43:16.689
Oh, I'm sorry.

43:17.816 --> 43:20.234
Take that!

43:26.908 --> 43:29.493
Are you all right?

43:34.250 --> 43:36.835
Under! After him.

43:38.921 --> 43:40.922
Get off!

43:41.632 --> 43:45.302
Oh, my dear chap. Awfully
sorry. Are you all right?

43:51.685 --> 43:53.645
Gotcha!

44:03.655 --> 44:07.741
Well done. And thank
you, gentlemen.

44:07.742 --> 44:11.079
Damn thieves. They're everywhere.

44:19.547 --> 44:23.299
- Did you wax them?
- Not a prayer. Not a bloody prayer.

44:23.300 --> 44:25.677
Never crack that crib.

44:25.678 --> 44:29.264
- Not in daylight.
- I said it was impossible.

44:29.265 --> 44:32.143
- What about night?
- Night!

44:34.270 --> 44:37.106
I've marked this crib
for three nights.

44:37.107 --> 44:41.527
There's a jack at the top
of the stairs all night long.

44:46.950 --> 44:52.873
He talks to the constable making his
rounds... but he doesn't leave his post.

44:56.669 --> 45:00.797
Then at two o'clock he
takes his tightener.

45:23.113 --> 45:28.117
And right at 2.30 he goes off to
relieve himself from his bottle of beer.

45:28.118 --> 45:30.704
And that's when I time him.

45:32.706 --> 45:37.044
I time him from when he goes
off to when he comes back.

45:49.348 --> 45:54.520
And it's been the same... three nights
running. A very regular bloke, is this jack.

46:05.824 --> 46:08.409
75 seconds.

46:08.701 --> 46:10.745
It's a coopered ken.

46:10.746 --> 46:16.376
You say you're the fastest screwsman
in the country. Well, here's a challenge.

46:16.377 --> 46:22.174
Challenge? 75 seconds for two keys?
It's nigh impossible.

46:22.508 --> 46:26.302
What if a snakesman comes over the
roof and cracks it from the inside?

46:26.303 --> 46:30.599
What snakesman's to break that drum?
Nobody good enough is out.

46:30.600 --> 46:32.351
The best is Clean
Willy and he's in.

46:32.352 --> 46:34.728
- Where's he in?
- Newgate Prison.

46:34.729 --> 46:37.440
And there's no escaping that.

46:42.111 --> 46:44.905
Only Willy can climb that.

46:45.365 --> 46:47.742
Shame he's in Newgate.

47:39.004 --> 47:42.507
No, guv, don't cut me. I'm goin'.

47:54.062 --> 47:57.481
Hello, dearie. Comin'
in for a good time?

47:57.482 --> 48:00.067
You won't be sorry.

48:26.386 --> 48:28.972
What's it to be, guv?

48:29.264 --> 48:31.266
Bit of a tickle for you?

48:31.267 --> 48:34.394
You dab it up with Clean
Willy the snakesman, right?

48:34.395 --> 48:36.980
I did. He's in Newgate now.

48:36.981 --> 48:38.607
You visit?

48:38.608 --> 48:40.609
I do now and again.

48:40.610 --> 48:43.820
I visits as his sister, see?

48:43.821 --> 48:47.407
There's another of those if
you can downy him a message.

48:47.408 --> 48:49.701
What's it to be?

48:49.702 --> 48:54.707
- Tell Willy to break at the next topping.
- There's no breaks from Newgate!

48:54.708 --> 48:58.461
Tell him he breaks at the next
topping or he's not Clean Willy.

48:58.462 --> 49:02.256
Tell him to go to the house
where he first met John Simms.

49:02.257 --> 49:04.634
John Simms.

49:07.971 --> 49:10.557
Are you John Simms?

49:35.918 --> 49:39.962
Oh, my! I think I'm going to die.

49:39.963 --> 49:44.175
Oh, my! I think I'm going to die.

49:44.218 --> 49:48.346
Oh, my! I think I'm going to die.

49:49.181 --> 49:51.767
Fine day for a hanging.

49:52.268 --> 49:55.646
Do you really think he'll make it?

49:56.147 --> 49:58.732
- Did you bring the trimmings?
- It's all here.

49:58.733 --> 50:00.817
- Medicine?
- Everything.

50:00.818 --> 50:03.153
- Do you want some cold chicken?
- No.

50:03.154 --> 50:07.366
Willy's the best snakesman there is...
but he can't get out of there.

50:07.575 --> 50:10.912
Dearly beloved, wonder
not if the world hate you.

50:10.913 --> 50:15.666
We know that we have passed from death
to life because we love the brethren.

50:15.667 --> 50:18.544
He that loveth not
abideth in death.

50:18.545 --> 50:21.380
Whosoever hateth his
brother is a murderer.

50:21.381 --> 50:26.427
And you know that no murderer hath
eternal life abiding in himself.

50:26.428 --> 50:30.265
In this we have known
the charity of God.

51:06.595 --> 51:09.180
And in God's house...

51:14.854 --> 51:19.816
Goodness and mercy all my
life shall surely follow me...

51:19.817 --> 51:23.070
and in God's house forevermore...

51:24.030 --> 51:27.908
Oh, my! I think I'm going to die.

51:32.164 --> 51:35.041
They say Willy can
climb a wall of glass.

51:35.042 --> 51:38.295
